# Spring Boot REST API

Aligned with Spring Boot 4.0.x / Spring Framework 7.0.x.

## HTTP Semantics
- GET: read-only, cacheable. POST: create. PUT: replace. PATCH: partial update. DELETE: remove
- Resource URIs are nouns, plural: `/users`, `/orders/{id}`
- Never expose verbs in URIs (no `/getUser`, `/deleteOrder`)

## Status Codes
- 200 OK, 201 Created (with `Location` header), 204 No Content
- 400 Bad Request, 401 Unauthorized, 403 Forbidden, 404 Not Found, 409 Conflict
- 500 Internal Server Error (never intentionally return)

## DTOs and Records
- Use records for request/response DTOs
- Never expose domain entities directly in API responses
- ISO-8601 `Instant` for timestamps in DTOs

## Validation
- `@Valid` on request body parameters
- Bean Validation annotations: `@NotNull`, `@Size`, `@Pattern`
- Validate at the boundary, not deep in the domain

## Error Handling
- `@ControllerAdvice` with `@ExceptionHandler` for centralized error mapping
- RFC 9457 Problem Details for error responses
- Never expose stack traces or internal class names in API responses

## API-First (OpenAPI)
- `openapi.yaml` as the source of truth
- Generate interfaces with OpenAPI Generator (`useSpringBoot4` flag)
- Implement generated interfaces in `@RestController` classes

## Versioning and Deprecation
- URI path versioning (`/v1/users`) or header-based
- `Deprecation` and `Sunset` headers for deprecated endpoints

## Pagination
- Query params: `page`, `size`, `sort`
- Return total count and link headers or HATEOAS links

## HATEOAS
Use Spring HATEOAS for public APIs where discoverability and self-describing responses matter.

### When to Use
- Public APIs consumed by external clients
- APIs where link relations guide client navigation
- Hypermedia-driven workflows (state transitions via links)

### When to Skip
- Internal microservice-to-microservice APIs (overhead without benefit)
- Simple CRUD APIs with well-known, stable endpoints

### Implementation
```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/v1/orders")
public class OrderController {

    private final OrderModelAssembler assembler;

    @GetMapping("/{id}")
    public EntityModel<OrderResponse> getOrder(@PathVariable Long id) {
        var order = orderService.findById(id);
        return assembler.toModel(order);
    }

    @GetMapping
    public CollectionModel<EntityModel<OrderResponse>> listOrders(Pageable pageable) {
        var orders = orderService.findAll(pageable);
        return assembler.toCollectionModel(orders);
    }
}

@Component
public class OrderModelAssembler implements RepresentationModelAssembler<OrderResponse, EntityModel<OrderResponse>> {

    @Override
    public EntityModel<OrderResponse> toModel(OrderResponse order) {
        return EntityModel.of(order,
            linkTo(methodOn(OrderController.class).getOrder(order.id())).withSelfRel(),
            linkTo(methodOn(OrderController.class).listOrders(Pageable.unpaged())).withRel("orders"));
    }
}
```

### HAL Response Example
```json
{
  "id": 1,
  "description": "Order 1",
  "status": "CONFIRMED",
  "_links": {
    "self": { "href": "/api/v1/orders/1" },
    "orders": { "href": "/api/v1/orders" }
  }
}
```

